cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >
  If you use the AIRBDS AI-Readiness Dataset Scoring Metric in your work,
  please cite it using the metadata below.

title: "AIRBDS AI-Readiness Dataset Scoring Metric"
version: "0.3"
date-released: "2025"
license: CC-BY-4.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/gavinf97/airbds-metric"
url: "https://aibio.ac.uk/about/working-groups/airbds/"
abstract: >
  A structured, versioned checklist for evaluating the AI-readiness of
  bioscience datasets. Questions are grouped into four scopes
  (Infrastructure, Metadata, Content, Ethics) and weighted as Optional (2 pts),
  Important (5 pts), or Critical (80 pts) to produce a composite score and
  grade (Caution / Bronze / Silver / Gold). Developed by the AI-Ready
  Bioscience Datasets (AIRBDS) working group of the AIBIO-UK network,
  funded by BBSRC.

keywords:
  - AI-readiness
  - bioscience datasets
  - machine learning
  - data quality
  - FAIR data
  - metadata
  - scoring metric
  - AIBIO-UK

